            <title>[GROOVY-41] Logical &amp;&amp; expressions are not currently handled properly by the parser</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-41</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &amp;amp;&amp;amp; token in a logical expression seems to disappear, leaving half of the expression going through to the AST generator stuff.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (x &amp;gt; 1 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; y &amp;lt; 2) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;results in this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (x &amp;gt; 1) &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If you look into ParserTest at the test testLogicalAndExpression() and look at the console output you&apos;ll see what I mean.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
